When editing Summary missing-data warnings:

- Summary shows **one** gold `!` per row in the **Warning** column only (`TabSummary.lua`).
- **One** tooltip via `PresentMissingDataTooltip`; title format: `Some data for <name> has not been gathered yet.`
- All conditions aggregate in `GetMissingDataInfo` (`SummaryData.lua`); insert instructions with `addUniqueInstruction` (de-duped list).
- Warnings are **expected after version upgrades** until users log in and gather data; new conditions belong in `GetMissingDataInfo`, not new Summary columns.
- Do **not** add a second Summary column or separate tooltip pipeline for a subset of missing data.
- `GetTalentSpecMissingInfo` is for Gear compare only — not Summary UI.
- Gear/Reputation tab gear-score `!` marks (`ScoreSortRow.lua`) are a separate system.

Full architecture, anti-patterns, and add-condition checklist: `.cursor/skills/summary-missing-data/SKILL.md`.
